#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.14"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.14:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.14:0.2"
msgid "2. Balavagga"
msgstr "2. Powers"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: balavitthatasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.14:0.3"
msgid "14. Vitthatasutta"
msgstr "14. In Detail"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.14:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, balāni."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five powers."

msgctxt "an5.14:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.14:1.3"
msgid "Saddhābalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, satibalaṃ, samādhibalaṃ, paññābalaṃ."
msgstr "The powers of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.14:2.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, saddhābalaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the power of faith?"

msgctxt "an5.14:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has faith in the Realized One’s awakening:"

msgctxt "an5.14:2.3"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "an5.14:2.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, saddhābalaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the power of faith."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.14:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, vīriyabalaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the power of energy?"

msgctxt "an5.14:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo "
"anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant lives with energy roused up for giving up unskillful "
"qualities and gaining skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly "
"vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities."

msgctxt "an5.14:3.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, vīriyabalaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the power of energy."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.14:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, satibalaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the power of mindfulness?"

msgctxt "an5.14:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako satimā hoti paramena satinepakkena samannāgato, "
"cirakatampi cirabhāsitampi saritā anussaritā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a noble disciple is mindful. They have utmost mindfulness and "
"alertness, and can remember and recall what was said and done long ago."

msgctxt "an5.14:4.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, satibalaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the power of mindfulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.14:5.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, samādhibalaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the power of immersion?"

msgctxt "an5.14:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "an5.14:5.3"
msgid ""
"vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;"
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter "
"and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of "
"immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without "
"placing the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "an5.14:5.4"
msgid ""
"pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena "
"paṭisaṃvedeti yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti "
"tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;"
msgstr ""
"And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third "
"absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, "
"personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

msgctxt "an5.14:5.5"
msgid ""
"sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ "
"atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they "
"enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with "
"pure equanimity and mindfulness."

msgctxt "an5.14:5.6"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, samādhibalaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the power of immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.14:6.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, paññābalaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the power of wisdom?"

msgctxt "an5.14:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya "
"samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a noble disciple is wise. They have the wisdom of arising and "
"passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending "
"of suffering."

msgctxt "an5.14:6.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, paññābalaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the power of wisdom."

msgctxt "an5.14:6.4"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca balānī”ti."
msgstr "These are the five powers.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.14:6.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
